        "content": "<p>It's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Combinatorics/SimpleGraph/DegreeSum.html#SimpleGraph.sum_degrees_eq_twice_card_edges\">here</a></p>\n<p>I don't understand why it needs the <code>Fintype (Sym2 V)</code>. It can be deduced from <code>Fintype V</code>, I believe?<br>\nCan <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Finset/Sym.html#Sym2.instFintype\">this</a> be used?</p>",
        "id": 453457012,
        "sender_full_name": "Ilm훮rs C카rulis",
        "timestamp": 1721751133
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It can be stated with just Fintype V, but then if someone else has a different construction for Fintype (Sym2 V), they won't be able to use the lemma directly, they'll need to convert between the two</p>",
        "id": 453470107,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
